data.description: PRICE REDUCED! THE LOWEST PRICED HOUSE IN HARVESTON! Welcome to the idyllic Harveston Lake enclave in Temecula, where Aloha warmly embraces you into an exceptional living experience.  This enchanting abode opens with a captivating entryway, introducing an entertainer's dream kitchen adorned with pristine white cabinetry and exquisite granite countertops. A generously sized island accommodates four bar stools, perfect for culinary camaraderie. Stainless steel appliances gleam, and the kitchen seamlessly connects to a cozy family room with a fireplace.  Ascending to the upper level, you'll discover a spacious master bedroom featuring a balcony with neighborhood views. The master bathroom offers a separate shower, deep soaking tub, and dual sinks, all designed for convenience. His and hers walk-in closets ensure impeccable organization.  Additional bedrooms are gracefully situated on the second floor, with a conveniently located laundry room.  On the third floor, a captivating loft, currently a Rocky-themed movie room, awaits for leisure and entertainment, creating lasting memories.  Harveston Lake boasts its iconic lake, inviting exploration with walking and biking trails. The clubhouse features a swimming pool, spa, splash pad, and an outdoor fireplace for gatherings and celebrations. Sports enthusiasts can enjoy baseball and soccer fields, while playgrounds delight the little ones.  This property offers not only a splendid residence but also a vibrant lifestyle within a close-knit community. Minutes away, the Promenade Mall, restaurants, and shopping beckon. Wine enthusiasts can explore Temecula's renowned wine country, and thrill-seekers can visit the prestigious Pechanga casino.  In Harveston Lake, you'll discover a harmonious balance of serene living and city offerings. Come experience luxury, convenience, and natural beauty in perfect harmony. When you're considering a visit to the Somerville street address, please be aware that it leads you to the rear of the property, where the garage is situated. The main entrance to the house, however, is on Newport Road.
